parameters: \N<Zuuteruka>Lakebed ruins...?
\N<Senior Officer Ryuda>That's right.

\N<Zuuteruka>Unfortunately, I've never heard of them. What value could
there possibly be in some desolate ruins in a backwater
town?
\N<Senior Officer Ryuda>Investigating that is your mission.

\N<Senior Officer Ryuda>Those ruins may contain something that will solidify our
Ryuda's control. If you play your cards right, you might be
able to obtain it.
\N<Zuuteruka>...
A

\N<Senior Officer Ryuda>You're back, Zuuteruka. Let's hear the results of your
investigation of the underwater ruins without delay.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Well, it's not as much information as you might
have hoped for.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Captain, what kind of information has Zuuteruka brought
back?

\N<Tseda>Well, it's a separate unit's business, so I don't know the
details.

\N<Tseda>But from what I've heard, there's something in some remote
town that could solidify our Ryuda's control... That seems
to be the gist of it.
\N<Ryuda Soldier>What could that be...?
\N<Tseda>I don't know what it is, but doesn't it sound interesting?

\N<Tseda>If I could get my hands on it, it would be a big deal, a
real rise in status. It might be dubious, but don't you
think it's worth checking out?
\N<Ryuda Soldier>So... we're heading to this town you speak of?
\N<Tseda>Yes, that's the plan.
\N<Ryuda Soldier>But Captain, aren't you currently on a different mission?

\N<Tseda>Such trivial tasks, even if done diligently, won't amount to
any significant achievements. So why not take a chance on
the information Zuuteruka brought back?
\N<Ryuda Soldier>...You may be right. Understood, we will accompany you.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Heh, I've always wanted to be part of something bigger from
the start. I'll follow you anywhere!
\N<Tseda>Alright, that's the spirit.
\N<Rozaro>...Did you call for me?

\N<Senior Officer Ryuda>Yes... Tseda and his party have left the unit and headed for
the ruins in that town.

\N<Senior Officer Ryuda>He has always voiced dissatisfaction with the unit. Perhaps
this action is the first step towards rebellion.
\N<Rozaro>...

\N<Senior Officer Ryuda>Rozaro, you are skilled. Pursue Tseda's party and bring them
back in chains.

\N<Senior Officer Ryuda>Should you succeed in your mission, I will see to it that
you inherit all of Tseda's achievements and rewards to date.
\N<Rozaro>...Understood.
\N<Rozaro>Dissatisfaction with the unit... Rebellion, huh.

\N<Rozaro>If one is burdened with one thankless task after another,
it's natural to want to rebel.

\N<Rozaro>Hmph... To think I would sympathize with a rebel. Perhaps
it's time for me too... to consider my options.
